<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
The nuclear sequence data obtained for this study revealed three main clusters within the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Hartig" baseAuthorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Pristiphora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pristiphora carinata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Pristiphora carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group: 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. carinata" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. coactula" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="coactula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. coactula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. borea" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="borea">P. borea</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. groenblomi" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="groenblomi">P. groenblomi</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. albilabris" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="albilabris">P. albilabris</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 30" captionStartId="F30" captionText="Figure 30. Maximum likelihood tree of Pristiphora carinata group based on nuclear genes (NaK and POL 2). Numbers at branches show SH-aLRT support (%) / ultrafast bootstrap support (%) values. Values of only well supported branches (&gt; 90 for both) and of P. coactula clade with moderate support are shown. Letters &quot; f &quot; stand for &quot; female &quot;, &quot; m &quot; for &quot; male &quot;, and &quot; l &quot; for larva. Numbers at the end of the tip labels refer to sequence length and the number of heterozygous positions." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure30" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719541" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">30</figureCitation>
). No nuclear sequence data are yet available for 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. breadalbanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="breadalbanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. breadalbanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Cameron, 1882b) and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. lativentris" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="lativentris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. lativentris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Thomson, 1871). A nearly perfect match morphologically to the 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. trochantericus" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="trochantericus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">L. trochantericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
holotype is ZMUO.035514, which falls within the 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. coactula" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="coactula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. coactula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cluster based on nuclear DNA (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 30" captionStartId="F30" captionText="Figure 30. Maximum likelihood tree of Pristiphora carinata group based on nuclear genes (NaK and POL 2). Numbers at branches show SH-aLRT support (%) / ultrafast bootstrap support (%) values. Values of only well supported branches (&gt; 90 for both) and of P. coactula clade with moderate support are shown. Letters &quot; f &quot; stand for &quot; female &quot;, &quot; m &quot; for &quot; male &quot;, and &quot; l &quot; for larva. Numbers at the end of the tip labels refer to sequence length and the number of heterozygous positions." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure30" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719541" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">30</figureCitation>
). There are two main clusters based on COI sequences, one of which contains only 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. borea" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="borea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. borea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Konow, 1904) and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. groenblomi" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="groenblomi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. groenblomi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Lindqvist, 1952) and the other one all species (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 31" captionStartId="F31" captionText="Figure 31. Maximum likelihood tree of Pristiphora carinata group based on mitochondrial COI gene. Numbers at branches show SH-aLRT support (%) / ultrafast bootstrap support (%) values. Values of only well supported branches (&gt; 90 for both) are shown. Letters &quot; f &quot; stand for &quot; female &quot;, &quot; m &quot; for &quot; male &quot;, and &quot; l &quot; for larva. Numbers at the end of the tip labels refer to sequence length and the number of ambiguous positions." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure31" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719542" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">31</figureCitation>
). Within the COI cluster containing all species (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 31" captionStartId="F31" captionText="Figure 31. Maximum likelihood tree of Pristiphora carinata group based on mitochondrial COI gene. Numbers at branches show SH-aLRT support (%) / ultrafast bootstrap support (%) values. Values of only well supported branches (&gt; 90 for both) are shown. Letters &quot; f &quot; stand for &quot; female &quot;, &quot; m &quot; for &quot; male &quot;, and &quot; l &quot; for larva. Numbers at the end of the tip labels refer to sequence length and the number of ambiguous positions." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure31" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719542" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">31</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. borea" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="borea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. borea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. groenblomi" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="groenblomi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. groenblomi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. albilabris" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="albilabris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. albilabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Boheman, 1852) (
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Betula" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Betula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
feeders) tend to separate from 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. coactula" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="coactula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. coactula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Salix" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Salix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. carinata" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hartig, 1837) (
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Vaccinium" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vaccinium" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Vaccinium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Based on the specimens having nuclear data, the species (mainly females) of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Hartig" baseAuthorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Pristiphora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pristiphora carinata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Pristiphora carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group may be separated by the following key, although it might not always work for all specimens, particularly 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. coactula" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="coactula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. coactula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. borea" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="borea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. borea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Excluded from the key are the (sub)arctic species 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. breadalbanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="breadalbanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. breadalbanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. lativentris" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="lativentris">P. lativentris</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Pristiphora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pristiphora" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pristiphora</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1871" baseAuthorityName="C.G.Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Pristiphora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pristiphora lativentris" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lativentris">Pristiphora lativentris</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
may have somewhat different serrulae from the other species (almost papilliform, see fig. 215 in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/jhr.59.12656.figure3" author="Prous, M" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Hymenoptera Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 190" refId="B150" refString="Prous, M, Kramp, K, Vikberg, V, Liston, A, 2017. North-Western Palaearctic species of Pristiphora (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae). Journal of Hymenoptera Research 59: 1 - 190, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/jhr.59.12656.figure3" title="North-Western Palaearctic species of Pristiphora (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/jhr.59.12656.figure3" volume="59" year="2017">Prous et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). The identity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1882" baseAuthorityName="Cameron" baseAuthorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Pristiphora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pristiphora breadalbanensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breadalbanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Pristiphora breadalbanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(most similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. borea" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="borea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. borea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. coactula" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="coactula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. coactula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) needs further research to confirm if characters (e.g. structure of median mesoscutal lobes) mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Benson, RB" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B11" refString="Benson, RB, 1958. Hymenoptera, Symphyta. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 6(2c): 139-258." title="Hymenoptera, Symphyta. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 6 (2 c): 139 - 258." year="1958">Benson (1958)</bibRefCitation>
to separate this species are reliable.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure30" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719541" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" start="Figure 30" startId="F30">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Figure 30.</emphasis>
Maximum likelihood tree of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Hartig" baseAuthorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Pristiphora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pristiphora carinata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Pristiphora carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group based on nuclear genes (NaK and POL2). Numbers at branches show SH-aLRT support (%) / ultrafast bootstrap support (%) values. Values of only well supported branches (&gt;90 for both) and of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. coactula" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="coactula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. coactula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade with moderate support are shown. Letters &quot;f &quot; stand for 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“female”">&quot;female&quot;</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“m”">&quot;m&quot;</normalizedToken>
for 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“male”">&quot;male&quot;</normalizedToken>
, and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“l”">&quot;l&quot;</normalizedToken>
for larva. Numbers at the end of the tip labels refer to sequence length and the number of heterozygous positions.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption doi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure31" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719542" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" start="Figure 31" startId="F31">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Figure 31.</emphasis>
Maximum likelihood tree of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Hartig" baseAuthorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Pristiphora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pristiphora carinata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Pristiphora carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group based on mitochondrial COI gene. Numbers at branches show SH-aLRT support (%) / ultrafast bootstrap support (%) values. Values of only well supported branches (&gt;90 for both) are shown. Letters &quot;f &quot; stand for 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“female”">&quot;female&quot;</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“m”">&quot;m&quot;</normalizedToken>
for 
