<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
Examples of lancets of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. borea" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="borea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. borea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. carinata" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. coactula" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="coactula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. coactula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are shown in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 32" captionStartId="F32" captionText="Figure 32. Lancets of Pristiphora carinata group. A. P. coactula (ZMUO. 031490); B. P. borea (ZMUO. 033284); C. P. carinata (ZMUO. 031554)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719543" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">32A-C</figureCitation>
, but more specimens need to be examined to check if there are any consistent differences between the species. Morphological differences between the males of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. borea" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="borea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. borea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. carinata" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. coactula" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="coactula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. coactula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not clear. Externally, it seems that 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. coactula" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="coactula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. coactula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
tends to be paler (clypeus, pronotal angles, tegula, metafemur, and sternum 9 completely or mostly pale) than 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. borea" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="borea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. borea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. carinata" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The dorso-apical margin of the paravalva of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. borea" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="borea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. borea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="F34" captionText="Figure 34. Penis valves of Pristiphora carinata group. A. P. carinata (ZMUO. 031419); B. P. borea (DEI-GISHym 80148); C. P. groenblomi (DEI-GISHym 80210); D. P. coactula (ZMUO. 039225); E. P. coactula (DEI-GISHym 84186); F. P. albilabris (ZMUO. 032465)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure34" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719545" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">34B</figureCitation>
) may be more strongly inclined basally compared to 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. carinata" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. coactula" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="coactula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. coactula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differences between the penis valves of the latter two species are not clear (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="F34" captionText="Figure 34. Penis valves of Pristiphora carinata group. A. P. carinata (ZMUO. 031419); B. P. borea (DEI-GISHym 80148); C. P. groenblomi (DEI-GISHym 80210); D. P. coactula (ZMUO. 039225); E. P. coactula (DEI-GISHym 84186); F. P. albilabris (ZMUO. 032465)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure34" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719545" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">34A, D, E</figureCitation>
). The most distinctive penis valve in the 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. carinata" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group seems to belong to 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. albilabris" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="albilabris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. albilabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="F34" captionText="Figure 34. Penis valves of Pristiphora carinata group. A. P. carinata (ZMUO. 031419); B. P. borea (DEI-GISHym 80148); C. P. groenblomi (DEI-GISHym 80210); D. P. coactula (ZMUO. 039225); E. P. coactula (DEI-GISHym 84186); F. P. albilabris (ZMUO. 032465)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure34" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719545" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">34F</figureCitation>
), which has the most distinctly inclined dorso-apical margin of paravalva. Overall shape of penis valve of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. groenblomi" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="groenblomi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. groenblomi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="F34" captionText="Figure 34. Penis valves of Pristiphora carinata group. A. P. carinata (ZMUO. 031419); B. P. borea (DEI-GISHym 80148); C. P. groenblomi (DEI-GISHym 80210); D. P. coactula (ZMUO. 039225); E. P. coactula (DEI-GISHym 84186); F. P. albilabris (ZMUO. 032465)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure34" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719545" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">34C</figureCitation>
) is most similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. borea" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="borea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">P. borea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it may be larger.
</paragraph>
